1) Why is 3Q guide so conservative (0-2% comp implies 2yr decelerates by 7-9pp sequentially)?;  
2) Why would 3Q EBIT margin compress -20bp to flat after +120bp in 2Q, 80bp easier compares vs 2Q, and with packaway loaded (packaway inventory +41% YOY)?;  
3) With BURL now the 3rd offpricer to comment on strong August trends, what gives the company conviction in underlying consumer strength vs just a BTS pull forward?;  
4) Is there a \(12.00\) scenario for 2026 now? Offprice multiples should expand in the near-term in anticipation of easing compares in Sept/Oct (especially with early cold weather this week). We're bullish. But putting the usual frenzy of analysis around near-term comps aside...what is 2026 EPS power for this company? Consensus is \~\(11.00, is\)11.50 more appropriate given the momentum in the business? Is there a\)12.00$ bull case within reach?
